<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-5029] Latest (0.13.0) Node.js lib does not provide entry point</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-5029</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The latest published `thrift` version:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;does not contain &apos;index.js&apos; at the package root&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;has no &quot;main&quot; entry point in package.json&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;So module request throws an exception:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
require(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;thrift&apos;&lt;/span&gt;)
Thrown:
Error: Cannot find module &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;thrift&apos;&lt;/span&gt;
Require stack:
- &amp;lt;repl&amp;gt;
    at Function.Module._resolveFilename (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:625:15)
    at Function.Module._load (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:527:27)

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
