                            <comment id="17103928" author="emmenlau" created="Sun, 10 May 2020 19:33:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m very sorry but I&apos;m under the impression that this issue has been reported multiple times. Can you check if the following description and workaround help you?&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/61475375/thrift-npm-instalation-fails/61676953#61676953&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/61475375/thrift-npm-instalation-fails/61676953#61676953&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See also the linked related issues.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m sorry that the issue has not been fixed yet. It seems the maintainer of the official thrift npm package &quot;vanished&quot; and has not yet taken care of the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17111264" author="emmenlau" created="Tue, 19 May 2020 15:14:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In order to reduce the pressure on this issue, I&apos;ve published a snapshot of the current Apache Thrift trunk with many fixes and improvements to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.npmjs.com/package/@biodataanalysis/thrift-trunk&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.npmjs.com/package/@biodataanalysis/thrift-trunk&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please test this to see if it would suite your needs? Any feedback is more than welcome.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
